==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[acetum]]'' vinegar, from ''[[acere]]'' to be sour.

===Pronunciation===
'''a*ce-tous'''
{{rfap}}
AAH-seh-tuhs

===Adjective===
'''acetous'''

# Having a sour taste; sour; acid.
#:'''Quotations'''
#:*An '''acetous''' spirit - [[Boyle]]
#:*A liquid of an '''acetous''' kind - [[Bp. Lowth]]
# Causing, or connected with, [[acetification]]; as, '''acetous''' fermentation.

===Derived terms===
*'''Acetous acid''': a name formerly given to vinegar

